            <mods:abstract>The largest blue diamond in the world, pear-shaped and weighing 45.52 carats. According to legend, it is cursed and will bring misfortune to its owner. It was stolen in 1792 during the French Revolution by six thieves, and recovered 20 years later. The diamond has since belonged to several owners. Currently, it is displayed in the Smithsonian Museum of Natural History in Washington, D.C.</mods:abstract>
